Overview[edit | edit source]

Main article: Pay-to-play Woodcutting training

Woodcutting is heavily modified by two tier 1 relics.

  • Endless Harvest makes obtaining logs twice as fast and removes banking time.
  • Production Master is not directly beneficial to Woodcutting training.
  • Skilling Prodigy allows players to chop trees more quickly due to its +12 visible level boost.

Axes[edit | edit source]

Axes can be made using the Smithing skill. The following tables detail common methods to obtain axes in the Trailblazer League:

Axe Level Level[1] How to obtain in Misthalin
Bronze axe 1 1 Obtained with starting gear. May be purchased at Bob's Brilliant Axes in Lumbridge for 1 GP. Can be easily obtained from many sources.
Iron axe 1 1 May be purchased at Bob's Brilliant Axes in Lumbridge for 56 GP.
Steel axe 6 5 May be purchased at Bob's Brilliant Axes in Lumbridge for 200 GP.
Black axe 11 10 Reward casket (easy) or rarely from reward casket (beginner). Uncommon drop from abyssal demon with level 85 Slayer.
Mithril axe 21 20 Common drop from tree spirits in the Enchanted Valley. May be created with level 51 Smithing.
Adamant axe 31 30 Common drop from tree spirits in the Enchanted Valley, or rarely from reward casket (medium). May be created with level 71 Smithing.
Rune axe 41 40 Uncommon drop from tree spirits in the Enchanted Valley (1/32), or rarely from reward casket (hard). May be created with level 86 Smithing.
Dragon axe 61 60 Unobtainable in Misthalin. See below.
  1. ↑ The listed Attack levels are only required to wield the axes, not use them.

Other equipment[edit | edit source]

Item Region Notes
Machetes Karamja✓ Can be used to cut light jungle, medium jungle, and dense jungle. Needed for the Tai Bwo Wannai Cleanup minigame and to enter the Kharazi Jungle.
Lumberjack outfit Morytania✓ The full set, when worn, grants a 2.5% bonus Woodcutting experience. Obtainable from the Temple Trekking minigame.
Kandarin headgear Kandarin✓ Chance to double logs from normal trees. 10% extra experience when cutting maple trees in Seers' Village, except for the Kandarin headgear 1.
Strung rabbit foot Kandarin✓ Slightly increases bird's eggs and rings when receiving a bird nest. Does not increase the drop rate of bird nests.
Dragon axe Fremennik✓ Boosts Woodcutting by 3. Only obtainable from Dagannoth Rex, Dagannoth Prime, or Dagannoth Supreme.
Infernal axe Fremennik✓
Asgarnia✓		 Boosts Woodcutting by 3. Requires 85 Firemaking, a dragon axe, and Cerberus' smouldering stones, which may also be obtained from hellhounds albeit very rarely.
Crystal axe Fremennik✓
Tirannwn✓		 Boosts Woodcutting by 3. Requires a dragon axe and a crystal tool seed from Zalcano. Consumes crystal shards.

Temporary boosts[edit | edit source]

Item Region Notes
Spicy stew (brown spice) Desert✓ Boosts Woodcutting by ±0-5. Requires manual completion of the Freeing Evil Dave subquest in Recipe for Disaster.
Dragon axe Fremennik✓ Boosts Woodcutting by 3. Only obtainable from Dagannoth Rex, Dagannoth Prime, or Dagannoth Supreme.
Axeman's folly Morytania✓ Fremennik✓ Boosts Woodcutting by 1. Requires the Morytania or Fremennik region to brew with level 49 Cooking.
Axeman's folly(m) Morytania✓ Fremennik✓ Boosts Woodcutting by 2. Requires the Morytania or Fremennik region to brew with level 49 Cooking, more easily produced by using the stuff from Trouble Brewing.

Item Region Master Notes
